sion in St Etienne,\\\" the NZOC said on Tuesday.\", \"from\": 897, \"to\": 1029, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 937, \"end\": 948, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.6295159879084234, \"rank\": 0.5845315051624835, \"text\": \"New Zealand\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_women's_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 991, \"end\": 1001, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Stephen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.213063092354052e-15, \"text\": \"St Etienne\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Stephen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Stephen\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"July\", \"from\": 901, \"to\": 905}, {\"ngram\": \"a drone\", \"from\": 910, \"to\": 917}, {\"ngram\": \"the NZOC\", \"from\": 1004, \"to\": 1012}, {\"ngram\": \"Tuesday\", \"from\": 1021, \"to\": 1028}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Team support members immediately reported the incident to police, leading to the drone operator, who has been identified as a support staff member of the widerCanadian Women's football team,to be detained.\\\"\", \"from\": 1031, \"to\": 1238, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Team support members\", \"from\": 1032, \"to\": 1052}, {\"ngram\": \"the incident\", \"from\": 1074, \"to\": 1086}, {\"ngram\": \"the drone operator\", \"from\": 1109, \"to\": 1127}, {\"ngram\": \"a support staff member\", \"from\": 1156, \"to\": 1178}, {\"ngram\": \"the widerCanadian Women's football team\", \"from\": 1182, \"to\": 1221}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The incident was immediately reported to theInternational Olympic Committee's integrity unit and Team Canada has since apologised.\", \"from\": 1240, \"to\": 1370, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1337, \"